sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin as Administrator
    participant App as Kiosk App (Virtual or Physical)
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant VB as Vision Box (Kiosk A)

    Note over App,API: Scenario A: Kiosk Boot Sequence
    Note over API,VB: ConnectionManager enforces strict single-connection-per-kiosk rule (reconnecting Vision Box forcibly closes the previous socket)
    App->>API: GET /api/v1/kiosks/{kiosk_id}/lockers [With JWT Token]
    API->>DB: Fetch physical status of lockers
    DB-->>API: Statuses (e.g. AVAILABLE, MAINTENANCE, OCCUPIED)
    API-->>App: 200 OK (Kiosk UI renders current lockers)

    Note over Admin,VB: Scenario B: Admin Remote Control
    Admin->>App: Logs in and opens Kiosk Management [With JWT Admin Token]
    App->>API: GET /api/v1/kiosks
    API-->>App: 200 OK (List of all kiosks)

    Admin->>App: Selects Kiosk A -> Locker 1 -> "Force Open"
    App->>API: POST /api/v1/lockers/{locker_id}/open
    Note over API: Validates that the token holds the Admin role
    Note over API,VB: locker_id in WSS payload = logical_number (physical slot int), not the UUID
    API->>VB: WSS: open_slot {locker_id: logical_number}
    Note over API,VB: Fire-and-forget: audit log is written after send, not waiting for slot_opened
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO audit_logs {action_type: 'ADMIN_FORCED_OPEN'}
    API-->>App: 200 OK (Locker successfully opened)